roughout quarter, in-person September 12-14, 2019) END OF PROGRAM: Showcase and Job Fair (in-person, September 13, 2019) MHCID SCHEDULE 2019-2020 Year Rolling acceptances open now with a final application deadline of March 31, 2019 SEPTEMBER 9 to 13, 2019 Overview of HCI and Design (accelerated in-person, required to be in Irvine, all costs once you arrive to Irvine are covered by program) FALL: User Needs Analysis (online); Design and Prototyping (online) WINTER: User Experience and Evaluation (online); Advanced Design and Prototyping (online) SPRING QUARTER: Interactive Technology Studio (online); Capstone Project, Advisory Board meeting, (in-person March T.B.D. and online throughout quarter) SUMMER QUARTER: Innovations in HCI and Design (online); Capstone Project (online throughout quarter, in-person T.B.D.) END OF PROGRAM: Showcase and Job Fair (in-person, T.B.D) Please contact mhciddirector@ics.uci.edu for further information. Feedback Privacy Policy Â© 2019 UC Regents